I think the individual schools themselves and and the individual needs of your daughters are more important than generalisations about education and single-sex or co-ed schools. 
However, if you want an opinon from a general education pespective, and you can read up on this, the general rule is that single sex schools are better for the academic performance of your daughters. Research is quite clear about this. For a variety of reasons, boys in a classroom has an overall negative impact on girls' learning. 